Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of accepting a bribe. I acknowledge my involvement in accepting a total of 4000 pounds in exchange for not publishing an article that revealed the true emissions of a company. I accept full responsibility for my actions.

I accepted the bribe with the intention of withholding the information about the company's emissions, which exceeded their claims by one million tonnes of CO2 per year. However, I do not believe this had a significant effect as the true numbers were released by someone else just five weeks later. Therefore, it is clear that my actions did not have long-lasting consequences.

Prior to this incident, I had a clean record, aside from a single speeding ticket. I understand the seriousness of this offense and deeply regret violating the law.

In conclusion, I plead guilty to the offense of accepting a bribe and accept the consequences of my actions. While I recognize the need for accountability, I leave the determination of an appropriate sentence in the hands of the court.

Thank you for your attention.
